com.sap.conn.idoc.jco

Class JCoIDoc

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.conn.idoc.jco.JCoIDoc

  • public abstract class JCoIDoc
extends Object
    The SAP Java IDoc Library provides an API to send, receive and process IDocs.

    To make use of this library you have to install both: the SAP Java IDoc Library 3.1 and the SAP Java Connector 3.1 Standalone.

    Version:
    3.1

      • getIDocRepository

        public static IDocRepository getIDocRepository(JCoDestination destination)
                                        throws JCoException
        Returns the IDocRepository instance for the specified destination. If such an IDocRepository instance does not exist yet a new one will be created. For each repository destination a IDocRepository instance is kept in the cache.
        Parameters:
        destination - The JCo destination.
        Returns:
        The IDoc repository.
        Throws:
        JCoException - in case of a failure when creating the IDocRepository instance.
        NullPointerException - if the passed destination is null.

        Parameters:

      • send

        public static void send(IDocDocument idoc,
                        char idocVersion,
                        JCoDestination destination,
                        String tid)
                 throws JCoException
        Sends a single IDoc document to the destination by using the given tid.
        Parameters:
        idoc - The IDoc document to send.
        idocVersion - The IDoc version. For example, use IDocFactory.IDOC_VERSION_DEFAULT for the default version.
        destination - Destination to the target system.
        tid - Transaction ID.
        Throws:
        JCoException - in case of a failure while sending the IDoc document.
        NullPointerException - if the passed destination or the IDoc document is null.
        See Also:
        IDocFactory

      • send

        public static void send(IDocDocument idoc,
                        char idocVersion,
                        JCoDestination destination,
                        String tid,
                        String queueName)
                 throws JCoException
        Sends a single IDoc document to the destination by using the given tid and queueName. In case you want to queue the IDoc on the IDoc application layer, use IDocFactory.IDOC_VERSION_3_IN_QUEUE for the idocVersion argument. This certainly requires in addition that the queueName is neither null nor empty.
        Parameters:
        idoc - The IDoc document to send.
        idocVersion - The IDoc version. For example, use IDocFactory.IDOC_VERSION_DEFAULT for the default version or IDocFactory.IDOC_VERSION_3_IN_QUEUE for IDoc application layer queueing.
        destination - Destination to the target system.
        tid - Transaction ID.
        queueName - An optional parameter used in case when the IDoc document shall be sent via queued RFC (qRFC). This name is also used as the queue name at IDoc application layer queueing.
        Throws:
        JCoException - in case of a failure while sending the IDoc document.
        NullPointerException - if the passed destination or the IDoc document is null.
        See Also:
        IDocFactory
